==Old English==
===Etymology===
Common Germanic ''*namōn'', from Proto-Indo-European ''*(H₁/H₃)no-mn̥''.  Cognates include Greek '''[[ὄνομα]]''' (''onoma'') and Latin [[nomen|nōmen]].  

